    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-11-23T20:34:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-11-23T20:34:00-05:00" n="238"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d238">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/5728: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The President of the Technical Board</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_SJF1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stevens</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Harbin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-11-24T10:00:00+08:26">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 24, 1919, 10 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 6:11 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Information previous cables confirmed Reds at Omsk captured 35,000 soldiers, 10
                    generals, 1,000 officers, 2,000 machine guns, 3,000,000 shells, 1,000,000
                    rifles, shells, uniforms and equipment for 30,000 men, 16 armored trains.
                        <persName corresp="#p_KAAV1">Kolchak</persName> army is entirely demoralized
                    and scattered. Czechs have all left <persName corresp="#p_YGNN1">Novo Nicholas
                            [<hi rend="italic">Novo Nikolaievsk</hi>]</persName> and foreigners with
                    them. It is probable that Reds will capture 157 trains now on the way east. I
                    see no chance for the Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SJF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stevens</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
